column2: Rie Ikeda Davidovitch /  Rie Ikeda- Davidovitch
column18: On November 29 2003, Rie Ikeda took her son to Japan and never returned to Canada.
In cooperation with the FBI

In April 2011, both parents traveled with their son Aleksander to visit the mother's family in Poland. The father returned to Canada on his own May 13 2011. The mother, Elzbieta Nowacki and child did not return to Canada. Nowacki is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Abduction.
Fei Wing Tsang is wanted for four counts of assault with a weapon, four counts of forcible confinement and three counts of kidnapping in 1995.
Jean Yves Tremblay, along with 25 other accomplices, is a suspect in a multiple murder that occurred in Lennoxville, Quebec in 1985 when five members of the Hells Angels were murdered.

column12: Conspiracy to Import/Export a Controlled SubstanceDrug Offences
column18: Ralph Duval is wanted in connection with Projet Colisée, an international investigation project established to destabilize organized crime and more specifically, the Rizzuto Clan. This significant investigation, which took place between 2002 and 2006 was conducted by the Unité mixte d'enquête sur le crime organisé (UMECO), an RCMP initiative composed of several law enforcement agencies.

Mohammed Sodagari is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for two counts of sexual assault against a 21 year old female. Sodagari was charged in this matter but failed to attend court. He was educated as an engineer in Iran and was working in a factory while in Canada.

On July 12 2009, at approximately 3am, a woman in her mid 20s was walking alone and talking on her cell phone on Squirrel Street in Banff, Alberta. She was approached from behind by a male who tapped her on the shoulder. The male smashed her cell phone and suddenly threw her to the ground and sexually assaulted her. She screamed and fought back, scratching at the mans face and gouging his eyes. He punched her four times in the face and head before running away.

On January 31 1994, Tan Tieu Hong had an altercation with a waiter at a Toronto restaurant, at which time Hong threatened to kill the waiter. Hong left the restaurant but returned later that night armed with a handgun. Hong shot his victim, leaving him paralyzed from the waist down. Tan Tieu Hong is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Attempted Murder.

column2: Heyle Cruz Pendome /  Heylel Pendome Cruz /  Heyle Perdomo Cruz /  Heyler Perdomo
column18: On March 12 1994, Heylel Cruz was thrown out of a night club in Montreal following a fight. A few minutes later, Cruz returned to the club armed with a gun and shot the doorman in the chest. The victim died in hospital. Heylel Cruz fled and is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Second Degree Murder.

While impersonating a police officer, Jacek Ludwik Pyszniak tricked his victim into exiting his vehicle. Once the victim was outside the vehicle Pyszniak shot him four times. He was charged with Attempted Murder and ordered to stand trial. Pyszniak went missing a few days prior to the start of his trial. He is still at large.

column2: Abdoulkadi Musse /  Abdoulkadi Ali Musse /  Abdoulkadir Ali Musse /  Abdi Abdul Kadir Mousse
column18: On August 24 1994, Nellie Bobbish was found dead in a Montréal home that she occupied with her boyfriend Abdoulkadi Ali Musse. The victim had been stabbed several times. Musse was seen leaving the premises. Abdoulkadi Ali Musse is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Second Degree Murder.

On March 18 2005, while driving his vehicle Ary Batalha struck Ben Kozak, a 42 year old man who was walking his dog across Carling Avenue in Ottawa. Both Kozak and his dog were killed. Police arrested Batalha and charged him with impaired driving and dangerous driving causing death.
Wanted for the abduction of his son, Alex Gonzales. Alex was abducted on August 23 1991.
Wanted for the 1996 parental abduction of his daughter, Nina Akbarian. Believed to be in Iran.

column2: Marejnejad Hossein /  Hoseein Marej Nejad /  John Marejnejad
column12: Invitation to Sexual TouchingSexual AssaultSexual Offences
column18: Hossein Marejnejad was born in Iran. He previously worked at and owned a convenience store and an Iranian restaurant. He was possibly spotted in Auckland New Zealand and seen in Tonga (South Pacific).
Wanted on a Canada-wide warrant for Sexual Assault and Extortion.

On July 13 2006, police responded to a call at a residential apartment and discovered the victim Malena Morales, deceased with obvious signs of trauma to the body. A Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for her husband Henry Stanley Morales. The accused is believed to have fled the country to Mexico and may have since escaped to Ecuador, Guatemala, Panama, El Salvador or the southern United States (Texas).

John Alan Joseph Tucsok is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for multiple sex offences involving female youths. Tucsok was a church elder in Ontario and sexually assaulted female youths associated with the church over a 4 year period. He may still be a member of, or associating with Christian groups. Tucsok was at large on bail when he fled Ontario in 2003. He was last known to be in the Calgary area.
Gioncondo Napoli was convicted of trafficking narcotics in 1981. He served federal jail time before being released on parole, at which time he disappeared. Gioncondo has family living in Italy.

column2: Ashor Sadeh Shleimon /  Shur Sadeh Shalemon
column18: Ashor Sadeth Shleimon is known to have participated in two robberies and was sentenced to over 6 years in jail. Less than a year after his release from prison, he breached his parole and has not been seen since.

On February 25 2005, Richmond RCMP were made aware of a local limousine driver, Morteza Izadifar who was luring at risk teenagers by providing them with free limousine rides, cash and alcohol. He often entertained these youths in his Vancouver apartment and engaged in inappropriate sexual activities. It is estimated that these assaults occurred between 1999-2002. Izadifar is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Sexual Assault and Sexual Interference With a Person Under 14. Police believe he may have returned to the Middle East, possibly Iran.
On October 14 2008, Ma sexually assaulted a woman at his residence. When she attempted to escape he choked her until she lost consciousness. It is believed that Ma may have fled to Eastern Canada.

column2: Liban Abdinassir Sheikhadem /  Liban Abdinassi Sheikhadem /  Liban Abdem Nasser Sheikhadem /  P A C
column18: On July 31 2011, Ottawa Police responded to a stabbing in the downtown area. Upon arrival, officers and paramedics found a male unconscious and bleeding. The male was rushed to hospital where he was pronounced dead. The investigation led to the identification of Liban Sheikhadem as the suspect in the crime. Sheikhadem has a history of violence and drug possession.

column2: Brian Black /  Manuel Nico Ortega /  Benzo / " B"
column18: Conor D'Monte is believed to be a high ranking member of the United Nations Gang. He is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for the slaying of rival gang member Kevin LeClair. D'Monte is also wanted for the Conspiracy to Murder the Bacon Brothers and/or their associates. D'Monte is known to frequent Vancouver, Edmonton, Calgary, Toronto and Montreal Canada. He is also known to travel to Spain and Asia. Conor D'Monte is associated to a drug network in Mexico and he was last seen in the Vancouver area in January 2011.

On October 24 1993, Hossein Ghoodjani called 9-1-1 from his home in Toronto and told the police communications operator that he had killed his wife with a rope. Police officers attending the scene met Ghoodjani at the door and found Dorys Delgadillo unconscious and not breathing. Emergency Medical Services and Fire Department personnel managed to revive the victim but she died in hospital later that day. Hossein Ghoodjani was charged with First Degree Murder. The accused absconded during the preliminary hearing and is currently wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant.

column2: White,  Anthony /  Richards,  Randy /  Carter,  Jason Michael /  Blackwood,  Richie /  Stitch
column18: On May 7th, 2018, Toronto Police Service received a call for a personal injury collision. A male victim, Christopher Reid was located at the scene and found to have sustained several gunshot wounds. He was taken to the hospital and May 10th, 2018 was pronounced dead. A vehicle of interest had been located through video surveillance and through investigation. Richie Blackwood was identified as a primary suspect and a Canada Wide warrant was issued for his arrest.
On June 4 2005, Romana Dittrichova contravened a custody order when she travelled to the Czech Republic with her three children: Adam Dittrich, Ludvik Dittrich and Robert Dittrich.

Following "Projet Chapitre" targeting a criminal organization specializing in cloning and distributing forged credit cards, Satheesan SHANMUGARAJAH is presently wanted for conspiracy (5 counts), fraud over $5000 (3 counts), possession of instrument for copying credit card data (3 counts), forging or falsifying credit cards, commission of an offence for a criminal organization and participation in activities of a criminal organization.
Reward : $25,000

After a sidewalk altercation, Mohamud Abukar Hagi shot and killed his victim and fled the scene. The firearm was recovered and an investigation identified Hagi as the accused. A Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for Hagis arrest. He has been sighted in Toronto and Windsor, Ontario, but he remains at large. Hagi has access to firearms.

In the early morning of January 18th, 2018, the victim attended a residential apartment to socialize with persons he knew. At approximately 3 am, the accused, Ali Omer MOHAMED attended the same apartment and started drinking with the victim. Just before 6 am, MOHAMED and the victim became embroiled in an argument which led to the accused shooting the victim. The victim sustained a fatal gunshot to the torso. Subsequent to investigation, MOHAMED was charged with second degree murder and a Warrant was issued for his arrest. It is believed that on or around January 23rd, 2018, the accused fled Canada to Djibouti and may have travelled to Somalia or Ethiopia.

column2: Nickolas Alex Kiriopoulos /  Andreas Alex Kiriopoulos /  Andy Liriopoulos /  Nicolaos Alex Kiriopoulos
column12: Possession of a Controlled Substance for Purpose of Trafficking
column18: Toronto's Project OB investigation identified Nicolaos Kiriopoulos as one of several individuals involved in cocaine and heroin trafficking. The project resulted in numerous arrests and seizures of firearms and narcotics. Kiriopoulos fled to Greece prior to his arrest. He has family ties in the Lagoon City area of Ontario. Kiriopoulos is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for numerous drug possession and trafficking charges.

On April 22 2002, Savang Sychantha and an accomplice beat a male victim to death and disposed of the body in a bush lot. The police investigation revealed that Sychantha was involved in the illicit drug trade and the victim was in financial debt to the suspect. Sychantha fled to Asia following this offence but it is believed that he may have returned to Canada and is potentially living under an assumed name and identity.

Mike Widziak began sexually assaulting his daughter at the age of 13. This behaviour continued for the next 3 years progressing further and becoming more violent until police were made aware. Widziak was arrested but has failed to appear for these charges and it is unknown where he is. Mike Widziak is originally from Poland and regularly made visits.

Suk Woon Lee's original offence is Second Degree Murder. He was facing deportation to Korea at the time of his absconment. On March 10 1990, Lee's wife drove the subject to the airport. She was under the impression he was traveling to Bangkok, Thailand, however his whereabouts remain unknown. Lee has a political science degree and is believed to be employed as a minister.

column2: Roman Vaclav Starostik /  Ronan Vaclav Starostik /  Vaclav Roman Starstik
column18: Vaclav Roman Starostik was the head of one of the worlds largest trafficking organizations. He was serving a life sentence for Conspiracy to Traffic Heroin and was on parole when he absconded in 2004. Starostik has access money from the proceeds of crime. He was last known to be in Czech Republic.

Marko Anicic was serving a five year sentence for carrying a concealed weapon, possession of a prohibited weapon and trafficking in a narcotic. Anicic was granted an unescorted temporary absence permit to visit his family in Toronto but failed to return.

column2: John Scott Henderson /  Brian Joseph Mc Connell
column18: McConnell is serving a two year, seven month sentence for Production of a Controlled Substance. His current status is listed as Suspended UAL.

On December 6 2005, several males were involved in an altercation at a karaoke club in downtown Ottawa, Ontario. During the altercation Fu Kwok Wei produced a handgun and shot two victims, then fled the scene. Wei is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warant for two counts of First Degree Murder.

On September 4 2003, an associate of Michel Abbaudi Estephan's was attacked and killed by several male suspects at an arcade in Ottawa. Estephan responded by shooting at the subjects with a handgun. He was apprehended by police and charged with attempted murder and numerous other charges. Estephan fled after being released from custody on bail.

On November 18 2010, Varaporn Toassami departed Vancouver with her daughter Chonticha Galame Ellefson-Toassami, and flew to Bangkok, Thailand. Varaporn Toassami has failed to return to Canada with her daughter.

On September 9 2005, Neon Daneyon Jemmott and an accomplice attempted to rob two men during a drug transaction in a Toronto area apartment. The victims were both shot during this altercation, one was fatally wounded. The surviving victim assisted police in identifying the suspects. One suspect was apprehended by police. Neon Daneyon Jemmott remains at large and is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for First Degree Murder.

Ferid Ahmed Imam is a former student of Biochemistry at the University of Manitoba. He was considered to be a well liked and respected member of the community and had no involvement in criminal activity prior to leaving Canada. In March 2007, Imam departed Canada for Pakistan where he became involved as a weapons instructor at a terrorist training camp aligned with Al Qaida. According to RCMP interviews, Imam was positively identified as an Al Qaida weapons instructor using the alias "Yousef". An RCMP witness interview showed that Imam's objective in joining a terrorist organization and obtaining weapons training was to fight and kill NATO soldiers in Afghanistan. He was last seen in the town of Miran Shah, Pakistan.

column2: Nguye,  Nken Cuon Manh /  Nguyen,  Cuong Manh /  Nguyen,  Cong Manh
column18: Ken Nguyen is currently serving a life sentence for second degree murder of a rival Asian gang member in 1999.

George Balgobin was arrested in 1998 in Toronto, Ontario for importing narcotics. He served federal jail time before being released on parole, at which time he fled. Balgobin was born in Guyana, South America and has family in Canada.
Wanted for commission of offence for terrorist group x2, conspiracy, participation in activity of terrorist group x2 and facilitating terrorist activity.
Richard Gleeson served a six year sentence for manslaughter that he committed in 1995. He has been wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Parole Violation since 2000.

column2: Anwar Ismail Abdalle /  Abdikarim Ismal Ashoor
column18: On March 4 2000, Ashoor was working as a taxi driver in Fort McMurray Alberta when he allegedly sexually assaulted a young woman. Ashoor was arrested and released on bail, but then failed to attend court and fled the jurisdiction.

Charles Billone sexually assaulted his 9 year old stepdaughter for approximately 3 years, stopping only after his daughter spoke to police. He is also believed to have committed further sexual assaults against his step daughter's friend. Billone was arrested on this matter but was released prior to attending court. Billone never returned to attend court and is currently wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for Sexual Assault, Sexual Interference and Fail to Attend Court.

On February 21 1981, a subject by the name of John Gleason was found in the state of mummified decomposition in the basement of a local building in Ottawa. An autopsy revealed that the subject had been stabbed approximately 50 times in the front and back torso and had his throat slit from ear to ear. After further investigation into the murder, it was revealed that Gregory Pictou was a primary assailant in the attack on Gleason. A Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for his arrest for Murder.

Wael Yousif Ali Al Jallad is wanted on several assault charges, including two counts of assault with a weapon. In the fall of 2000, he was convicted on all charges. Al Jallad failed to attend his sentencing date and a Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for his arrest.

column2: Christian Paul Landeta /  Anthony Davies Tedroy /  Tedroy Anthony Richardo /  Christian Pacel Ladeta
column18: Tedroy Davis' criminal convictions include robbery, weapon offences and aggravated assault. He served jail time for these offences and absconded while on parole.
Wanted for conspiracy, participation in activity of terrorist group and leaving Canada to participate in activity of a terrorist group.

Fernando Lemagueresse is wanted Canada-Wide for multiple counts of Sexual Assault, Sexual Assault Causing Bodily Harm, Sexual Interference and Sexual Exploitation. Lemagueresse committed these crimes against his daughter and step daughters over the course of several years of their childhood. He has ties in Toronto, Montreal and Chile. In 2010, Lemagueresse attempted to return to Canada from Chile, but canceled his flight after receiving information that the police were looking for him.

column2: Bergstaller,  Christian Gerhard /  Bergstaller,  Christian Gehard /  Bergstaller,  Gehard Christian
column18: Bergstaller committed multiple frauds at various financial institutions in the Lower Mainland between July 2017 – December 2017. Bergstaller opened various accounts in different names and saturated the accounts with fraudulent cheque deposits and committed fraudulent cash withdrawals. Bergstaller is currently wanted Canada Wide out of Vancouver, British Columbia.

On July 4 2011, Babak Ghanad murdered an 18 year old Toronto area woman. Ghanad then drove to Mexico where he boarded a flight to Germany, then continued on to Tehran, Iran. Ghanad is a truck driver by trade with no fixed address. He travelled extensively along the East coast from Canada to Florida, as well as through Western Canada into California and Texas. Ghanad spent time in Indonesia before coming to Canada. Police believe he is currently in Iran.
Wanted for the 1997 parental abduction of her daughter, Christina Isabella Lima. Believed to be in Greece.

column2: Vijay Manickavasagar /  Vijay Manickavaragar /  Vijayarajah Manickavasagar /  Vijayarajah Prabakaran /  Vijayaraja Rantham /  Bullet
column18: On March 20 2004, Amretta Singh was shot to death after returning home from a Brampton night club. She was shot in retaliation for a dispute that occured between her brother and two male suspects at the night club. The investigation identified Vijayaraja Manickavasagar as the shooter and a Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for his arrest. Police believe Manickavasagar may have traveled to Sri Lanka under a false passport.
Wanted for the 1999 parental abduction of his child, Kashmin Patel. Believed to be in India.

Andre Fernando Riquelme was involved in a fight that broke out in the west end of Toronto, resulting in three individuals being shot, one of whom did not survive. Riquelme is wanted for First Degree Murder and two counts of Attempted Murder in relation to this event.
David Carroll is a known member of the Hells Angels criminal organization.

Guido Hans Joachim Metzger is alleged to have committed sexual assaults against young people who were known to him in the late 1970s. Metzger failed to attend court in 1988. A Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for failing to appear and two counts of indecent assault. Police information indicates that he may have fled to Guyana.

Roxanne Eliana Yanez Parada and her son Jadon Alexander Yanez Parada left Canada to visit relatives in Chile and did not return. The child's father has full custody and Canadian courts have ordered that the child be returned. Roxanne Yanez Parada is believed to be in Chile.

In November 1991, Edgard Elias entered a convenience store armed with a handgun and robbed the store clerk. When the store clerk made a motion towards the counter, Elias shot the victim in the head and abdomen. Elias turned and pointed the gun at another employee, then ran from the store. The victim was deceased when police arrived. Elias was later identified as the accused and has an outstanding Canada-Wide Warrant for his arrest.

On April 29, 2011, the Ontario Superior Court convicted Emmanuel FEUERWERKER under the Criminal Code of Canada for Fraud over $5000 Section 380(1)(a), Possession of Property Obtained by Crime Section 354(1) and Laundering Proceeds of Crime Section 462.31(a). As of July 15, 2011, FEUERWERKER has failed to appear in court for his sentencing and he is now wanted Canada Wide. FEUERWERKER has connections with other fraudsters in the Toronto area.

column2: Gordon Gregg Armour /  Donald Armour /  George Lyln Britt /  George Liebers /  Donald Jay David Scott /  David Anderson /  Don Anderson /  Gary T Jordan /  James Theodore Oliver /  Jim Oliver
column18: In 1989, George Armour was sentenced to 2 years for False Pretences, Forged Documents and Failing to Comply. While on parole, Armour left Canada and fled to South America and to the United States. Armour has been employed in a variety of jobs both in South America and in the United States.

On March 17 1995, Joseph Ewudzi Woode was gunned down by Samuel Kwablah Tamatey as he left his residence in Etobicoke, Ontario. Tamatey is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for First Degree Murder. He is believed to be hiding in his native country Ghana.

On March 10 1993, Norman Needham shot and killed Dave Sylvester Francis. The victims body was dumped over the guardrail of a highway on-ramp and was discovered three weeks later. In April 1993, an arrest warrant was issued charging Norman Needham with Manslaughter. He is believed to have fled to Jamaica.
Surjid Singh Presto is a first time federal offender serving a life sentence for murder which occurred in June of 1974, as a result of a dispute between he and his landlord.

Peng Victor Li is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for First Degree Murder in connection to a beating death of a Markham Ontario teenager. Li has connections in British Columbia and in China and is believed to be using a passport in his alias name: Hao Lu.

column2: Joanna Vanbijsterveld /  Johanna Van Bysterveld /  Johanna Vanbysterveld
column18: On March 18 2005, Joanna Catharina Van Bijsterveld abducted her daughter Maria Rosa Di Valerio. Van Bijsterveld does not have custody of the child.
Take no action to apprehend this person yourself. Report any information to the nearest RCMP detachment or the police in your area or contact Crime Stoppers at 1-800-222-8477.

Robert Donald Joseph Armstrong has a history of assault, narcotics possessions and assaults on peace officers. He is presently wanted for escaping custody while being held on a charge of murder. His previous occupations include automobile purchasing agent, photographer and labourer.
Lisa Santana is wanted for Second Degree Murder. She is known to be violent so caution is urged when approaching subject. She is believed to be in Mexico.

column2: Mohsen Amir Dadgar- Kiani /  Mohsen Dadgar Kiani /  Mohsen Dadger- Kiai
column18: Mohsen Dadgar-Kiani has been charged with numerous criminal offences against his ex-wife but was permitted supervised visits with their two children. On May 20 1996, Dadgar-Kiani took his daughter to a shopping mall in Ottawa Ontario and from there proceeded with a well planned escape route and managed to flee to Iran. The daughter has since been returned to Canada. Moshen Dadgar-Kiani is still wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for parental abduction and several other criminal offences.

On February 12 1999, the RCMP were made aware of juvenile sexual assaults involving two young male victims that took place in several Canadian provinces over a period of time. These assaults started in the winter of 1973 and continued until the fall of 1977. The juvenile victims were sexually assaulted numerous times by an adult male, Jaroslav Krumlik, a Czechoslovakian who resided in the United States and Canada.

column12: Possession of a Controlled Substance for Purpose of TraffickingProduction of a Controlled Substance
column18: On July 15 2010, while executing a search warrant at a residence in New Brunswick, police discovered a large scale marihuana grow operation where over 1,600 marihuana plants were seized. Luo Li Shi was the only occupant of the residence. He was held in custody but released on bail on July 22 2010 and is currently wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant. Shi is a Chinese citizen and Canada Border Services Agency has also issued a Canada-Wide Warrant for his arrest. Shi's last know address was in Scarborough Ontario.

On April 4, 2018 the Abbotsford Police engaged in an investigation of parental abduction. Investigators discovered that on March 24, 2018 Wissam Tarabichi took his two children, daughter aged 9 yrs and son aged 8 yrs, to Seattle WA, USA. All three crossed the Canadian/USA border near Abbotsford BC. The following day Tarabichi and his children boarded a plane in Seattle and flew to Beirut Lebanon. As a result of the investigation Tarabichi was charged with Abduction in Contravention of a Custody Order, Section 282 CCC.

Wanted for counterfeiting, possession of prohibited weapon, manufacture fraudulent credit cards, use of forged credit cards, possession of credit card data (2 counts), possession of instrument for copying credit card data, possession of instrument for forging or falsifying credit cards, possession of property obtained by crime, forgery, uttering forged documents, possession of identity information with the intent to commit an indictable offence, distribution of identify information with the intent to commit a criminal offence, conspiracy to commit an indictable offence (4 counts), participation in activities of a criminal organization, trafficking in substance- cocaine (2 counts) and possession for purpose of trafficking- cocaine

column12: Conspiracy to Participate in Terrorist ActivitesTerrorist Activities
column18: Maiwand Yar is a former student of Mechanical Engineering at the University of Manitoba. In 2007, it is believed that Yar departed Canada with accomplice Ferid Ahmed Imam for Pakistan. According to witnesses, Yar advised that he and Imam were going to ally themselves with the Taliban and attend a terrorist training camp in order to receive instruction on firearms, explosives and guerilla warfare. Their specific objective for joining the Taliban was to fight and kill NATO (North Atlantic Treaty Organization) soldiers in Afghanistan. In a letter sent in 2009, Yar stated that he had in fact spent time in both the Taliban and Al Qaida.

Sawaran Singh Sekhon is wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant for the shooting death of Devinder Singh Gill that occurred in the early hours of Friday, September 11 2009 in Brampton Ontario. Sekhon may have fled to the area of Gilla (Ludhiana) in India.
Chieko Teton was with her husband Henrik and their one year old son Takaya in 2013 on vacation in Yokohama, Japan.

On April 2 2009, a Canada-Wide warrant was issued for Edyta Watkins for the abduction of her two children, Alexander and Christopher Watkins. Investigation has revealed that the mother took the children to the United States where they boarded a plane and flew to Germany. Edyta Watkins has connections in Poland, Germany, Austria, Czech Republic and the United States. She and the children are believed to be in Poland.
Kam Cheung Fung was serving a fourteen year sentence for conspiracy to traffic narcotics. While on an escorted leave permit, Fung escaped from the escorting correctional officer.

column2: Claudio Di Metteo /  Claudio D Imatto
column18: Claudio DiMatteo has a history of drug and fraud charges from the mid-1970s to early 1980s. In 1984 he was released from jail and was under mandatory supervision while living and working in Toronto, Ontario. DiMatteo disappeared in 1985.
Sergius Joseph Maher was serving a six year sentence for manslaughter. He breached his parole and has been wanted on a Canada-Wide Warrant since 1982.

Kin Chuen Tommy Ho was serving an 18 year sentence for drug import and trafficking offences. Ho was released on parole in 2005 and was meeting his release conditions until he absconded in 2006. He is believed to have connections in China, Hong Kong and Australia.

On March 2 2004, Andrei Ejov physically attacked a male victim and beat him with a baseball bat. Under the assumption that the victim was dead, Ejov placed the lifeless body into a hockey bag, only to realize that he was still alive. Ejov removed him from the bag and drove him to a hospital, where the victim later recovered. It is believed that Ejov may have fled back to Russia. A Canada-Wide Warrant of arrest was issued against Ejov for Attempted Murder and Aggravated Assault.

On October 18 1991, Abdi Aliow Elmi conned a 20 year old female into going to his apartment where he brutally beat and sexually assaulted her. Elmi was arrested and released on a recognizance before the court. He breached his recognizance and a Canada-Wide Warrant has been issued for his arrest.

column12: Conspiracy to Import/Export a Controlled Substance
column18: A sixteen month undercover operation was conducted in the greater Toronto area from July 1996 to October 1997. The case was a joint effort between the RCMP and Peel Regional Police. The operation culminated in the seizure of three hundred kilograms of cocaine valued at 90 million dollars. It was the largest seizure ever in the region of Peel. It severely disrupted a cell of Colombian based traffickers, three of whom have already pleaded guilty. Kratc-Usman was a high ranking representative of a cocaine organization in South America. He was in Canada to evaluate the Canadian operation and gave the final approval before the traffickers attempted to smuggle in the cocaine. The RCMP consider Kratc-Usman to be among the very upper echelon of international cocaine traffickers.

On April 13 2004, during a domestic argument with his common-law wife, Jeffrey Paul Emery poured a bottle of hairspray over her then set her on fire. She suffered third-degree burns to her legs, torso, arms and face and much of her hair was burned away. Emery refused to take her to the hospital. North Vancouver RCMP were alerted to the incident more than a month later when a relative contacted police. Emery was arrested, but absconded in December 2004 during an adjournment of his court case. He was convicted in absentia of aggravated assault and a Canada-Wide Warrant was issued for his arrest.
